FBIS3-52667 "drnes004__a94007" FBIS-NES-94-004-A Document Type:Daily Report 6 January 1994 ANNEX Israel Rabin Opposes U.S. Forces on Golan, Borders TA0501114594 Tel Aviv MA'ARIV in Hebrew 5 Jan 94 p 3--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY TA0501114594 Tel Aviv MA'ARIV Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Report by Hemi Shalev and Washington-based correspondent Avino'am Bar-Yosef] [Excerpt] Sources in the prime minister's bureau yesterday confirmed that Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin is not enthusiastic about the idea of posting U.S. troops on the Golan Heights. In a closed-door discussion held in the last few days Rabin also referred to the Palestinian desire for deploying U.S. forces at the border crossing points: "I do not want any American mother to cry on our account." Rabin adduced the example of U.S. intervention in Somalia, recalling the grave impact that the death of only a handful of American soldiers had on U.S. public opinion. [passage omitted]
